{
  "diffMode": "binary",
  "formatName": "LUKS Encrypted Volume",
  "version": "1.0",
  "extensions": [ ".img", ".luks" ],
  "description": "LUKS (Linux Unified Key Setup) encrypted disk volume format. Magic: 6 bytes 'LUKS' + 0xBA 0xBE (0x4C554B53BABE). LUKS1 header (592 bytes total): magic (6B), version uint16 BE = 1, cipher_name (32B ASCII e.g. 'aes'), cipher_mode (32B ASCII e.g. 'xts-plain64'), hash_spec (32B ASCII e.g. 'sha256'), payload_offset (4B BE — first data sector), key_bytes (4B BE: 16/24/32 for 128/192/256-bit AES), mk_digest (20B), mk_digest_salt (32B), mk_digest_iterations (4B BE), uuid (40B ASCII). Followed by 8 key slot structures of 48 bytes each. LUKS2 uses the same magic with version=2 and adds a JSON metadata area after the header.",
  "category": "Crypto",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "LastUpdated": "2026-04-15",
  "preferredEditor": "HexEditor",
  "references": [
    "https://gitlab.com/cryptsetup/cryptsetup/-/wikis/LUKS-standard/on-disk-format.pdf",
    "https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man8/cryptsetup.8.html"
  ],
  "detection": {
    "signatures": [
      {
        "value": "4C554B53BABE",
        "offset": 0,
        "label": "LUKS magic + 0xBA 0xBE — LUKS encrypted volume header magic (6 bytes)",
        "weight": 1.0
      }
    ],
    "matchMode": "any",
    "MinimumScore": 0.9,
    "Strength": "Strong"
  },
  "variables": {},
  "blocks": [
    {
      "name": "luksMagic",
      "offset": 0,
      "size": 6,
      "type": "bytes",
      "description": "LUKS magic identifier — 6 bytes at offset 0: ASCII 'LUKS' (0x4C 0x55 0x4B 0x53) followed by 0xBA 0xBE; this 6-byte sequence is the mandatory magic for all LUKS version 1 and version 2 encrypted volume headers",
      "storeAs": "luksMagic"
    },
    {
      "name": "luksVersion",
      "offset": 6,
      "size": 2,
      "type": "uint16",
      "endian": "BE",
      "description": "LUKS format version — 2-byte big-endian unsigned integer at offset 6; value 1 indicates LUKS1 with a fixed 592-byte header; value 2 indicates LUKS2 with an extended JSON metadata area after the binary header",
      "storeAs": "luksVersion",
      "valueMap": {
        "1": "LUKS1 — standard 592-byte header",
        "2": "LUKS2 — extended JSON header"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "cipherName",
      "offset": 8,
      "size": 32,
      "type": "ascii",
      "description": "Cipher algorithm name — 32-byte null-terminated ASCII string at offset 8 specifying the symmetric cipher used for disk encryption; typical values are 'aes', 'twofish', or 'serpent'",
      "storeAs": "cipherName"
    },
    {
      "name": "cipherMode",
      "offset": 40,
      "size": 32,
      "type": "ascii",
      "description": "Cipher mode and IV specification — 32-byte null-terminated ASCII string at offset 40 specifying the block cipher mode and initialization vector generation method; typical values are 'xts-plain64', 'cbc-essiv:sha256'",
      "storeAs": "cipherMode"
    },
    {
      "name": "hashSpec",
      "offset": 72,
      "size": 32,
      "type": "ascii",
      "description": "Hash algorithm specification — 32-byte null-terminated ASCII string at offset 72 specifying the hash function used for PBKDF2 key derivation; typical values are 'sha256', 'sha512', 'sha1', 'ripemd160'",
      "storeAs": "hashSpec"
    },
    {
      "name": "payloadOffset",
      "offset": 104,
      "size": 4,
      "type": "uint32",
      "endian": "BE",
      "description": "Payload sector offset — 4-byte big-endian unsigned integer at offset 104 indicating the sector number (512-byte sectors by default) where the encrypted data payload begins; header and key slots occupy sectors before this offset",
      "storeAs": "payloadOffset"
    },
    {
      "name": "keyBytes",
      "offset": 108,
      "size": 4,
      "type": "uint32",
      "endian": "BE",
      "description": "Master key length — 4-byte big-endian unsigned integer at offset 108 specifying the length in bytes of the master encryption key; 16=128-bit AES, 24=192-bit AES, 32=256-bit AES",
      "storeAs": "keyBytes",
      "valueMap": {
        "16": "128-bit AES",
        "24": "192-bit AES",
        "32": "256-bit AES"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "mkDigest",
      "offset": 112,
      "size": 20,
      "type": "bytes",
      "description": "Master key digest — 20-byte hash value at offset 112 used to verify that the correct master key has been derived from a passphrase; computed as PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA1 of the master key with mk_digest_salt"
    },
    {
      "name": "mkDigestSalt",
      "offset": 132,
      "size": 32,
      "type": "bytes",
      "description": "Master key digest salt — 32-byte random salt at offset 132 used in the PBKDF2 computation for the master key digest verification; unique per volume, stored in plaintext in the header"
    },
    {
      "name": "luksUuid",
      "offset": 168,
      "size": 40,
      "type": "ascii",
      "description": "Volume UUID — 40-byte null-terminated ASCII string at offset 168 containing the UUID uniquely identifying this LUKS volume; format is standard UUID with hyphens e.g. 'xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx'",
      "storeAs": "luksUuid"
    }
  ],
  "assertions": [
    {
      "name": "MagicValid",
      "expression": "luksMagic[0] == 0x4C && luksMagic[1] == 0x55 && luksMagic[2] == 0x4B && luksMagic[3] == 0x53 && luksMagic[4] == 0xBA && luksMagic[5] == 0xBE",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "LUKS magic at offset 0 must be exactly 4C 55 4B 53 BA BE ('LUKS' + 0xBA 0xBE); file is not a valid LUKS encrypted volume"
    },
    {
      "name": "VersionValid",
      "expression": "luksVersion == 1 || luksVersion == 2",
      "severity": "error",
      "message": "LUKS version at offset 6 must be 1 (LUKS1) or 2 (LUKS2); unknown version number indicates an unsupported or corrupt header"
    },
    {
      "name": "KeyBytesValid",
      "expression": "keyBytes == 16 || keyBytes == 24 || keyBytes == 32",
      "severity": "warning",
      "message": "Master key size at offset 108 should be 16 (128-bit), 24 (192-bit), or 32 (256-bit) bytes; non-standard key size may indicate a corrupt header or unusual cipher configuration"
    }
  ],
  "navigation": {
    "anchors": [
      { "name": "LUKS Header", "offset": 0, "size": 208, "description": "Main LUKS header fields: magic, version, cipher, hash, UUID, and digest" },
      { "name": "Key Slots", "offset": 208, "size": 384, "description": "8 key slot structures of 48 bytes each (offsets 208-591); each slot can hold one passphrase" },
      { "name": "Payload", "offset": -1, "size": -1, "description": "Encrypted data payload beginning at payloadOffset sectors; all bytes are ciphertext" }
    ]
  },
  "inspector": {
    "badge": "LUKS",
    "primaryField": "luksUuid",
    "showQualityScore": true,
    "groups": [
      {
        "name": "Identity",
        "fields": [ "luksMagic", "luksVersion", "luksUuid" ]
      },
      {
        "name": "Crypto Parameters",
        "fields": [ "cipherName", "cipherMode", "hashSpec", "keyBytes" ]
      },
      {
        "name": "Layout",
        "fields": [ "payloadOffset" ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "exportTemplates": [
    {
      "name": "Volume Summary",
      "format": "text",
      "template": "LUKS Encrypted Volume\nVersion: LUKS{luksVersion}\nUUID: {luksUuid}\nCipher: {cipherName} / {cipherMode}\nHash: {hashSpec}\nKey Size: {keyBytes} bytes\nPayload at sector: {payloadOffset}"
    },
    {
      "name": "Crypto Parameters CSV",
      "format": "csv",
      "template": "Field,Value\nVersion,{luksVersion}\nUUID,{luksUuid}\nCipher,{cipherName}\nCipherMode,{cipherMode}\nHash,{hashSpec}\nKeyBytes,{keyBytes}\nPayloadOffset,{payloadOffset}"
    }
  ],
  "forensic": {
    "riskLevel": "high",
    "notes": "LUKS full-disk encryption volume. Cipher name, mode, hash spec, and UUID are stored in plaintext in the header. Master key is protected by PBKDF2-derived key encryption in up to 8 key slots. Without a passphrase the payload is computationally infeasible to decrypt. UUID can link this volume to other forensic artifacts."
  },
  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "LUKS stores cryptographic parameters in a plaintext header even though the data payload is fully encrypted. For forensic analysis: extract the UUID to correlate with system logs, identify the cipher and hash for cryptanalytic assessment, check how many key slots are active (active slot has a specific iteration count), and note payloadOffset to determine where the key material area ends and data begins.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify 6-byte LUKS magic (4C 55 4B 53 BA BE) at offset 0",
      "Read version at offset 6 (BE uint16): 1=LUKS1 fixed header, 2=LUKS2 with JSON extension",
      "Read cipher name at offset 8 and cipher mode at offset 40 for encryption algorithm",
      "Read hash spec at offset 72 for PBKDF2 hash function used in key derivation",
      "Read UUID at offset 168 (40 bytes ASCII) for volume correlation in forensic context",
      "Check key slot structures at offsets 208-591 to determine which slots are active"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    { "name": "cryptsetup", "url": "https://gitlab.com/cryptsetup/cryptsetup", "role": "volume manager" },
    { "name": "dm-crypt", "url": "https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/admin-guide/device-mapper/dm-crypt.html", "role": "kernel driver" }
  ],
  "formatRelationships": [
    { "format": "VERACRYPT", "relation": "alternative — VeraCrypt volumes use plausible deniability with no visible header; LUKS stores plaintext metadata" }
  ],
  "MimeTypes": [ "application/x-luks" ],
  "UseCases": [
    "Linux full-disk encryption with cryptsetup",
    "Encrypted container file forensic analysis",
    "Cipher and key parameter extraction for security auditing"
  ],
  "QualityMetrics": {
    "CompletenessScore": 92,
    "DocumentationLevel": "detailed",
    "LastUpdated": "2026-04-15"
  },
  "TechnicalDetails": {
    "headerSize": 592,
    "magicOffset": 0,
    "magicBytes": "4C554B53BABE",
    "endianness": "big-endian",
    "keySlots": 8,
    "keySlotSize": 48,
    "notes": "LUKS1 header is 592 bytes with 8 key slots. LUKS2 extends this with JSON metadata. Big-endian byte order for all header integers. The payload_offset field is in 512-byte sectors. Each active key slot contains an encrypted copy of the master key."
  }
}
